The Web Application is available at:
https://ui-portfolio-eight.vercel.app/
# UI Portfolio - Ezekiel Lokeru

A modern, responsive personal portfolio website for Ezekiel Lokeru, showcasing web development, app development, photography, and design skills.

## Features

- **Hero Section:** Introduction with call-to-action buttons.
- **Profile Section:** Bio, contact info, and social links.
- **Services:** Cards describing offered services.
- **Skills:** Progress bars for featured skills.
- **Features Section:** Highlights of expertise and an image.
- **Stats:** Key numbers (projects, hours, support, customers).
- **Portfolio Gallery:** Clickable image gallery with popup viewer.
- **Footer:** Brand logos.

## Technologies Used

- HTML5 & CSS3 ([index.html](index.html), [styles.css](styles.css))
- [Font Awesome](https://fontawesome.com/) for icons
- [Google Fonts - Inter](https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Inter)
- [Magnific Popup](https://dimsemenov.com/plugins/magnific-popup/) for image gallery popups
- [jQuery](https://jquery.com/) for DOM manipulation

## Setup & Running Locally

1. **Clone or Download the Repository**

   Download the project files to your local machine.

2. **Project Structure**

   ```
   index.html
   styles.css
   images/
     audi.png
     benz.png
     Ezekiel-2.png
     Ezekiel.jpg
     featuresimage.jpg
     header.jpg
     mazda.png
     skillsimage.jpg
     toyota.png
     work1.jpg
     work2.jpg
     work3.jpg
     work4.jpg
     work5.jpg
     work6.jpg
   ```

3. **Open in Browser**

   Simply open `index.html` in your web browser. No build step is required.

4. **Image Assets**

   Ensure the `images/` folder is in the same directory as `index.html` and contains all referenced images.

5. **Internet Connection**

   The project uses CDN links for Font Awesome, Google Fonts, jQuery, and Magnific Popup. An internet connection is required for these resources.

## Customization

- **Content:** Edit `index.html` to update your name, bio, services, skills, and images.
- **Styling:** Modify `styles.css` to change colors, layout, or fonts.
- **Images:** Replace images in the `images/` folder with your own portfolio and branding.

